main event: A bright object appeared like a shooting star in the Philippine Sea, broke into two pieces, and then burned up in the atmosphere.
interesting points: The object was observed for 15 seconds by a single witness.
The weather conditions were clear with a full moon.
The report concludes that the nature of the object is not conclusive based on the witness description.
The report was sent as an urgent communication to multiple military and communications entities.
The object was observed from a position of 22N 134E, falling in an east-west direction.
sighted object: a bright object like a shooting star
